  "body": "We still see the following error messages from time to time:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntime=\"2020-02-04T06:56:52Z\" level=info msg=\"error retrieving beacon committees response: rpc error: code = NotFound desc = Could not retrieve data for epoch 5684, perhaps --archive in the running beacon node is disabled\" module=rpc\r\ntime=\"2020-02-04T06:56:52Z\" level=info msg=\"error retrieving epoch participation statistics: rpc error: code = NotFound desc = Could not retrieve data for epoch 0, perhaps --archive in the running beacon node is disabled\" module=rpc\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis happens usually after restarting a node or during times of finality issues. Unfortunately even after restarting affected nodes we are unable to recover epoch statistics data for certain epochs.\r\n\r\nFor example around epoch 3017 our node was restarted and now returns a participation rate of 0 for that epoch, but there are around 600 attestations in this epoch.\r\n\r\nWe use the following rpc call: `GetValidatorParticipation(context.Background(), &ethpb.GetValidatorParticipationRequest{QueryFilter: &ethpb.GetValidatorParticipationRequest_Epoch{Epoch: 3017}})`\r\n\r\nsee https://beaconcha.in/epoch/3017\r\n\r\nhttps://api.prylabs.net/eth/v1alpha1/validators/participation?epoch=3017 returns the correct data for the epoch.",
